**Section 1: User Story**

- **Epic Story
**As a Notice Processing Officer who needs to follow up against notices in the OCMS, I want the OCMS to allow me to change the processing stage of a notice, so that the OCMS can revert to an earlier processing stage to resend reminders or escalate to speed up the processing of a notice.

- **User Stories 
****![](data:image/x-emf;base64,)
**
- **Key Functions &amp; Features**

| Functions | Description |
| --- | --- |
| Manual Change Processing Stage | Change Processing Stage is the function to allow the OICs to update the current stage of the notice processing workflow. The OCMS Staff Portal provides a user interface for authorised OICs to manually change the notice’s processing stage. |
| Manual Change Processing Stage via PLUS Staff Portal | The PLUS Staff Portal enables authorised officers from PLUS to request changes to a notice’s processing stage. OCMS validates these requests and updates the workflow accordingly, returning confirmation or error messages to PLUS. |

**Section 2: Manual Change Processing Stage**

**
2.1** **Use Case**

- The Change Processing Stage module allows OICs to manually change a notice's processing stage, which in turn changes its workflow.

- The OCMS Staff Portal has a Change Notice Processing Stage module that allows OCMS OICs to: Search for notice(s) to be updated with a new processing stage. 
- Display the search results which are applicable to change the new processing stage on screen.
- Change the new processing stage by selecting the notice and completing the new processing stage form. 
- Perform a validity check for the new processing stage is allowed to change before sending the change request to the OCMS backend.
- Retrieve and download the Change Notice Processing Stage Data Report from the backend to view the Notices that manually change the new processing stage.

- When the Change Processing Stage is initiated from the Portal, the OCMS Backend will: 
- Validate the request and update the previous processing stage and date, last processing stage and date, next processing stage and date of the notice in the VON table. Update the previous processing stage with the value stored in the last processing stage, update the last processing stage and the next processing stage with the new processing stage value.
- Update the amount payable, administration fees immediately.
- Generate the report for internal tracking
- Return the updated notice details (with the updated last processing stage and next processing stage) together with the report link to the OCMS Staff Portal.

-

2.3** **Change Notice Processing Stage Screen**

- The Change Processing Stage Screen is a function of the Change Processing Stage module in the OCMS Staff Portal. 

- The key function of the module is to enable OICs to update a notice's processing stage, which in turn changes its workflow.

- The Change Processing Stage screen provides the following features:
- Search for notice(s) to be updated with a new processing stage. (This section focuses on the search function.)
- Select the notice(s) and submit a stage change request by completing the new processing stage form. (Details of the form and validity check for stage change submission are described in Section 2.4)

- The Change Processing Stage screen allows OICs to search for notice(s) by entering one of the available search criteria. The system supports single-field searches (e.g., Notice Number, ID Number or Vehicle Number). It also supports combination-field searches, such as searching by Current Processing Stage together with the Date of Current Processing Stage and ID/Vehicle Number with Current Processing Stage.

| Search Parameter | Description | Sample Value |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Notice No. | Notice number. Alphanumeric, 10 chars including spaces Page will validate if Notice Number entered is in the correct format | 441000001X |
| ID No. | Identification type and number Alphanumeric, 20 chars | S1234567A |
| Vehicle No. | Vehicle license plate number. Alphanumeric, up to 14 chars including spaces Page will display the warning message "Number does not match the local vehicle number format." when the input does not match the local vehicle number format. Users can still proceed to search. | SNC7392R |
| Current Processing Stage | Drop-down list for user to select Processing Stage: NPA ROV DR3 ENA RD1 RD2 RR3 DN1 DN2 Note : The pre-court stages (CPC and CFC ) will be included in future. | RR3 |
| Date of Current Processing Stage | The page displays a date picker tool for user to select the date, month and year. | 25/02/2025 |

- After the user has entered the search data and submitted to the OCMS backend, the backend will: Retrieve the notice(s) from “ocms_valid_offence_notice” data table and “ocms_offence_notice_owner_driver” data table by applying the search filter to retrieve notice data and offender data
- If the record is found, check if the notice(s) are eligible to change the processing stage. If the notice(s) are eligible, return the matching notices with the details to the Staff Portal.
- If the record is not found or the notice(s) are not eligible for the change processing stage, return the error message to the Staff Portal.

- The Change Processing Stage screen displays the result notices when matching data is returned. The notices are shown in a list with their details, and each notice includes a checkbox for selection. The details displayed on the screen include:
- Notice No
- Offence Type 
- Offence Date and Time 
- Offender Address 
- Checkbox with label ‘Send DH/MHA check’ to indicate whether to send DH/MHA check
- Vehicle No. 
- Offender ID 
- Offender Name
- Current processing Stage 
- Current processing Date 
- Suspension Type
- Reason for Suspension

Note: Refer to Section 2.4.3 for Notice Details

**2.4** **Submission of the Notice Change Processing Stage**

- The OCMS OIC selects the notice(s) from the search notice list and clicks on the ‘Change Processing Stage’ button to initiate the manual change process stage.

- The OCMS Staff Portal redirects to the Change Notice Processing Stage Form Page, which displays two sections:List of selected Notice(s) with the details
- Change Notice Processing Details Form

- The OCMS Staff Portal validates that the selected new processing stage is allowed before submitting to the OCMS Backend.

- If the new processing stage is not valid for the notice(s), the OCMS Staff Portal displays the error message, prompting the OIC that those notices are not applicable for changing the processing stage. The user has to uncheck those notices(s) and submit again.

- If the new processing stage is valid to change, the OCMS Staff Portal display the summary page, enabling the OIC to review the selected notices and the new processing stage.

- Once the OIC confirms the change of the new processing stage on the summary page, the OCMS Staff Portal send a request to OCMS Backend to update the notice’s processing stage.

**2.5 Backend Processing for Change Notice Processing Stage Submission**

When a new change notice processing stage is initiated from the Staff Portal, the OCMS backend executes the stage transition :. 

- Validate the request and update the previous processing stage and date, last processing stage and date, next processing stage and date of the notice in the VON table. Updated the previous processing stage with the value stored in the last processing stage, update the last processing stage and the next processing stage with the new processing stage value. (e.g. when a notice is EMCONS from RR3 to RD1, the Last Processing Stage and Next Processing Stage will both be changed to RD1 immediately. Previous Processing Stage will then be RR3. Last Processing Stage will allow user to know the current processing stage of the notice upon EMCONS. Next Processing Stage to the same will allow system to pick it up for reminder sending. By comparing the Previous, Last and Next Processing stage, we will know if EMCONS was done,)
- Update the amount payable and payment acceptance immediately according.
- Save the change processing stage record in ‘ocms_change_processing_stage’ data table in DB
- Generate the report for internal tracking and response stage change updated notices with URL to download generated report.
**2.5.1 Backend Processin for Manual Change Processing Stage **

**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

NOTE: Due to page size limit, the full-sized image is appended.
![](data:image/x-emf;base64,)

| No. | Process | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| | Pre-condition | Staff Portal submits a manual stage change request via API to the backend. |
| 1 | Receive API Request | OCMS Backend receives the stage change request payload from the Staff Portal. |
| 2 | Validate Request Data | OCMS Backend validates the request data: a. Validate request format: Confirm that the incoming request data is complete and in the correct format. If it is invalid, return an “Invalid format” error message to the Staff Portal. b. Check required fields: Verify that all mandatory data fields are present. If missing, respond to Staff Portal with a Missing data error message. |
| 3 | Check the request is the initial request | OCMS Backend check whether the request is the initial change processing stage request. If it is the initial request, it proceed to Step 4 to check the notices has the existing stage change record. If it is the confirmation request to proceed the stage change of the notices that has existing record, it proceeds to Step 5 to perform stage change processing. |
| 4 | Check the notice has Existing Stage Change Record | OCMS Backend verify in the database whether a stage change record for the same notice exists for today: Query ocms_change_processing_stage table using the notice number and current date If the notice exists in the table, OCMS Backend respond to Staff Portal with a message — “Notice No. xxx has existing stage change update.” It will proceed to update after confirm with the user to update for the existing stage change update.If no record exists: OCMS proceed with processing the new stage change request. |
| 5 | Change Current and Next Processing Stage of Notice | OCMS Backend updates the previous, current and next processing stage for request notice(s) If the request is for multiple notices, process each record sequentially. Set the previous processing stage and previous processing date with the value stored in the last (current) processing stage and date. Update the last processing stage and the next processing stage with the new processing stage value in the VON data table (ocms_valid_offence_notice) and set the last and next_processing_date to the current date. Perform the DH/MHA eligibility check: If not allowed, update the DH/MHA check status (DH/MHA_check = N) in the ocms_offence_notice_owner_driver data table. Save the stage change request in the CPS table (ocms_change_processing_stage). Verify if the update succeeded: If update failed → the system add error to log and respond to Staff Portal with Change Processing Fail . If update succeeded → update the current notice record for report generation (fields include last, current and next_processing_stage, reason_for_change, remark, cre_date, cre_user_id). |
| 6 | Handling amount payable update | The OCMS Backend will validate the notice(s) after the stage change to determine whether the amount payable requires updating and then update the amount payable if needed. The backend will decide to update the amount payable based on the notice’s previous processing stage and its newly updated processing stage. The calculation of the amount payable for stage changes is detailed in Section 2.5.1.3. Please refer to that section for additional information. |
| 7 | Generate Change Notice Processing Stage Report | OCMS Backend generates and uploads the Change Notice Processing Stage Report: Prepare the stage change records for reporting. Generate the Change Notice Processing Stage Report in .xlsx format. If report generation fails, the system retries once to regenerate report. If retry still fails, the system add error to log and stop the sub-flow. Upload the generated report to Blob Storage and obtain the file URL. If upload fails, the system retry once. If retry still fails, the system add error to log and stop the sub-flow. If both generation and upload succeed, it proceeds with returning the report URL to the Staff Portal. |
| 8 | Respond with Report URL | Return the updated notice details together with the report URL to the Staff Portal. |
| 9 | Check for Errors | OCMS Backend checks if any errors occurred during the submission or processing. If errors are found, they are consolidated, and an error email will be sent to MGG &amp; ISG &amp; OCMS users If no errors occurred during processing, OCMS end the process. |

**Section 3 – Manual Stage Change Initiated by PLUS**

**3.1 Use case**

1. The Change Processing Stage refers to the scenario where PLUS triggers a request to OCMS to manually change a notice's processing stage, which in turn changes its workflow.

2. This occurs when PLUS officers need to change the current processing stage of a notice, and the change is carried out manually within the notice processing workflow.

3. The PLUS system will perform validation to decide whether a Notice is eligible for a stage change before the stage change request is sent to the OCMS Intranet Backend.

4. When the OCMS Intranet Backend receives a stage change request, it performs the following actions for change processing stage submission:

- Validate the request and update the last and next_processing_stage of the notice in the VON table to this new stage..
- Generate the report for internal tracking.
- Return the notice details (with the updated last and next_processing_stage) together with the report link to the OCMS Staff Portal
Note : 
Since PLUS is not allowed to change the stage to CFC and both OCMS and PLUS are also not allowed to change the stage to ENA, these options should not be displayed in the dropdown list of New Processing Stage.,

**3.2 Manual Change Processing Stage via PLUS Staff Portal Processing Flow**

**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

NOTE: Due to page size limit, the full-sized image is appended.

![](data:image/x-emf;base64,)

| No. | Process | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Pre-condition: Initiate Change Notice Processing Stage | The PLUS officer initiates the stage change request for the Notice(s) in PLUS Staff Portal. |
| 2 | Pre-condition: Check Eligibility | Check Eligibility | The PLUS system checks if the notice is applicable for change processing stage based on pre-defined rules and conditions. Note: The specific conditions/restrictions (e.g., allowed notice types, status/processing stage eligibility, validation criteria, and exceptions) will be documented in the PLUS requirements. |
| Check Eligibility |
| 3 | Pre-condition: PLUS sends Request to OCMS | If eligible, PLUS sends a request to OCMS Intranet Backend for Manual Change Processing Stage via API. |
| 4 | OCMS Receives Request | OCMS Intranet Backend receives the request routed through APIM. |
| 5 | Manual Stage Change Process in OCMS Backend | OCMS Intranet Backend process: Data Validation: OCMS verifies whether the request data has completed or missing required data. If the data validation failed, OCMS responds to PLUS with the error message. (e.g. Invalid format, Missing data). Check the notice is eligible for manual stage change: OCMS verifies whether the request notice(s) are eligible to change the new processing stage. If the notice does not meet the pre-defined eligible rule, OCMS responds with an error message along with the list of changeable and non-changeable notices. If the notice(s) are applicable to change, OCMS perform the change processing stage: (a) Update the notice’s last_processing_stage and next_processing_stage with the new processing stage. (b) Save the stage change request in the ocms_change_processing_stage table. (c) Generate Change Processing Stage Report for the internal review. Refer to Section 2.5 for details on OCMS Backend Real Time Action for Manual Stage Change. |
| 7 | Respond to PLUS | OCMS Backend Response to PLUS Manual Stage Change Submission Success After the change processing stage is completed, OCMS returns the updated notice(s) together with the report URL to PLUS. Manual Stage Change Submission Failed If inapplicable notice(s) are detected, OCMS responds with an error message and provides a list of both changeable and non-changeable notices. If the request stage change notice has an existing stage change update in the database for today. In this case, the OCMS backend returns a message to the PLUS Staff Portal to confirm to change: ‘Notice No. xxx has an existing stage change update.’ If the failure is due to other reasons, OCMS responds with an error message only. |
| 8 | Handling for Stage Change Status in PLUS | The PLUS backend receives the response and validates whether the status indicates success or failure. a) If the status is successful , the PLUS Staff Portal will display: The updated Stage Change Notice details A link to download the generated Stage Change Report b) If the status indicates failure , PLUS performs the following checks: If the failure is due to an existing stage change update , the system displays a confirmation message informing the user that a stage change update already exists for the notice and prompts the user to confirm whether to proceed with the stage change. If the failure is due to any other reason , the system displays a “Stage Change Failed” message along with the specific failure reason. |
